CORRECT - The \verb|+| operator is left-associative. The expression is evaluated from left to right.
\begin{enumerate}
\item \verb|"Result: " + 5| is evaluated first. Since one operand is a \verb|String|, this is string concatenation, resulting in \verb|"Result: 5"|.
\item \verb|"Result: 5" + 3| is evaluated next. Again, this is string concatenation, resulting in \verb|"Result: 53"|.
\end{enumerate}

