CORRECT - According to Java operator precedence, logical AND (\verb|&&|) is evaluated before logical OR (\verb|\|\||).
\begin{enumerate}
\item The expression \verb|b && c| (\verb|false && true|) is evaluated first, resulting in \verb|false|.
\item The expression becomes \verb|a || false| (\verb|true || false|).
\item This evaluates to \verb|true|.
\end{enumerate}

