\item The second operand is \verb|x < 2|, which is \verb|1 < 2|, also evaluating to \verb|true|.
\item The XOR operator returns \verb|true| if and only if its operands are different. Since both operands are the same (\verb|true|), the expression \verb|true ^ true| evaluates to \verb|false|.
\end{itemize}
